S.B. NO.
C.D. 1
1 (1) Require each county, in collaboration with the Hawaii
2 community development authority, to establish a summer
3 streets pilot program that temporarily closes
4 vehicular traffic and repurposes roads for pedestrian
5 and cyclist uses;
6 (2) Authorize each county to consult with the department
7 of health regarding best practices for developing the
8 pilot program;
9 (3) Require each county to submit an initial proposal to
10 the executive director of the Hawaii community
11 development authority;
12 (4) Require the Hawaii community development authority to
13 submit a report to the Legislature; and
14 (5) Appropriate funds for the pilot program.
15 SECTION 2. (a) Each county, in collaboration with the
16 Hawaii community development authority, shall establish a summer
17 streets pilot program that temporarily closes vehicular traffic
18 and repurposes roads for pedestrian and cyclist use, outdoor
19 events, temporary installations, and other community-driven
20 activities.
2026-2556 SB3029 CDl SMA.docx
