Page 4
S.B. NO.
C.D. 1
1 (b) In developing the summer streets pilot program, each
2 county shall identify and designate specific streets for
3 pedestrianization, prioritizing areas that will best benefit
4 from reduced vehicular traffic, and that are central to local
5 commerce, cultural activities, and community engagement. The
6 summer streets pilot program shall support sustainable
7 transportation options, including the provision of bike lanes
8 and enhanced pedestrian pathways. Each county may consult with
9 the department of health regarding the best practices for
10 developing the pilot program.
11 (c) Each county shall submit an initial proposal for the
12 summer streets pilot program, including locations, schedules for
13 road closures, types of activities and amenities to be provided,
14 and a breakdown of projected costs to the executive director of
15 the Hawaii community development authority no later than
16 March 31, 2027.
17 (d) The Hawaii community development authority shall
18 submit a report of its findings and recommendations, including
19 any proposed legislation, to the legislature no later than
20 July 1, 2027.
