1 SECTION 3. There is appropriated out of the general
2 revenues of the State of Hawaii the sum of $200,000 or so much
3 thereof as may be necessary for fiscal year 2026-2027 for the
4 Hawaii community development authority to allocate to each
5 county for the summer streets pilot program required by this
6 Act.
7 The sum appropriated shall be expended by the Hawaii
8 community development authority for the purposes of this Act.
9 SECTION 4. This Act shall take effect on July 1, 2026.
